## Overview

Fix Calendar component on Planning page to keep navigation bar frozen while only calendar view content scrolls internally.

---

## Problem Statement

### Current Behavior
On the Planning page, when viewing Week/Day/List views:
- The ENTIRE Widget content scrolls (navigation bar + calendar views)
- Calendar navigation (Previous/Next buttons, "November 2025") scrolls away
- View mode buttons (Month/Week/Day/List) scroll away
- User loses context of which month/view they're in

### User Expectation
**Stay Frozen (Always Visible):**
1. Planning page header ("Planning & Calendar" + description)
2. Widget header ("Calendar" title)
3. Calendar navigation bar (Previous, "November 2025", Month/Week/Day/List buttons, Next)

**Scroll Internally:**
- Only the calendar view content (day cells, time slots, event list)

### Root Cause
The Calendar component has its navigation bar INSIDE the Widget's scrollable content area. The entire calendar-widget div is in the scrollable zone, so navigation + views scroll together.

**Current Structure:**
```tsx
<Widget> {/* Widget.tsx */}
  <div className="flex-1 overflow-auto p-4"> {/* Scrollable content */}
    <div className="calendar-widget h-full flex flex-col">
      <div className="calendar-nav"> {/* Navigation - CURRENTLY SCROLLS ❌ */}
        {/* Previous, Month, View buttons, Next */}
      </div>
      <div className="flex-1 min-h-0"> {/* Calendar grid */}
        {/* MonthView/WeekView/DayView/AgendaView */}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Widget>
```

---

## Proposed Solution

### Restructure Calendar to Manage Own Scrolling

**New Structure:**
```tsx
<Widget>
  <div className="flex-1 overflow-auto"> {/* Remove p-4, Calendar manages padding */}
    <div className="calendar-widget h-full flex flex-col">
      {/* Navigation - FROZEN ✅ */}
      <div className="flex-shrink-0 px-4 pt-4">
        <div className="calendar-nav">
          {/* Previous, Month, View buttons, Next */}
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Calendar Grid - SCROLLABLE ✅ */}
      <div className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto px-4 pb-4">
        {/* MonthView/WeekView/DayView/AgendaView */}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Widget>
```

**Key Changes:**
1. Remove `p-4` from Widget content div (Calendar manages own padding)
2. Wrap calendar-nav in `flex-shrink-0 px-4 pt-4` (frozen, padded)
3. Wrap calendar grid in `flex-1 overflow-y-auto px-4 pb-4` (scrollable, padded)

